## 🏗️ Architecture & Design Patterns

### 1. Separation of Concerns
```
bot.py          ← Telegram UI layer (commands, messages, callbacks)
crypto_engine.py ← Pure cryptography (no Telegram dependencies)
document_store.py ← Data persistence (no crypto dependencies)
demo_cli.py     ← Testing layer (no Telegram needed)
```

### 2. Repository Pattern (document_store.py)
- Abstracts data storage behind an interface
- Can swap JSON → PostgreSQL without changing bot.py

### 3. Strategy Pattern
- CryptoEngine exposes consistent interface
- Multiple algorithms run in parallel, independently

### 4. Event-Driven Architecture (python-telegram-bot)
- Bot handlers respond to events (commands, file uploads, button clicks)
- Async/await prevents blocking on API calls

