## 🧪 Testing Approach

### Test Categories (26 total)
```
TestSHA256      (4 tests) — known hashes, empty input, avalanche effect, large files
TestHMAC        (4 tests) — correct HMAC, wrong key fails, timing-safety, empty data  
TestSHA3        (2 tests) — produces valid hash, differs from SHA-256
TestDocumentID  (3 tests) — format validation, reproducibility, filename sensitivity
TestFingerprint (3 tests) — all fields present, file size, tamper detection
TestMerkleRoot  (5 tests) — single hash, empty list, two hashes, determinism, order matters
TestDocumentStore (5 tests) — register/retrieve, find by hash, missing hash, user isolation, delete
```

### Testing Philosophy
- **Unit tests** — each crypto function tested independently
- **Known-value tests** — compare against Python's own hashlib expected values
- **Negative tests** — verify failures when expected (wrong key, tampered data)
- **Determinism tests** — same input must always produce same output

